#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:1
msgid "For Maintainability"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:3
msgid ""
"_Is the shape of the change sound, and will the next reader understand it "
"without archaeology?_"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:5
msgid ""
"This is the index of the **maintainability** guidelines. Each subsection is "
"its own page, and each entry below links a stable `short-name` to its "
"guideline, with a one-line gist so a reader (or a review tool) can grasp the "
"guideline before opening it."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:10
msgid "Index"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:12
msgid "**[Design](design.md)**"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:13
msgid ""
"[`single-responsibility`](design.md#single-responsibility): Each module, "
"type, or function has one reason to change; keep functions small and one "
"concept per file."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:14
msgid ""
"[`dry`](design.md#dry): Give every piece of knowledge a single "
"representation; eliminate duplication once a pattern recurs."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:15
msgid ""
"[`information-hiding`](design.md#information-hiding): Hide details behind "
"interfaces; expose only what consumers need."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:16
msgid ""
"[`open-closed`](design.md#open-closed): Extend stable modules through "
"existing interfaces; don't add extension points preemptively."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:17
msgid ""
"[`least-surprise`](design.md#least-surprise): Names, types, and APIs behave "
"as they suggest; prefer conventions users already know from Rust and Linux."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:18
msgid ""
"[`coupling-cohesion`](design.md#coupling-cohesion): Keep inter-module "
"connections small and visible; keep each module focused on one purpose."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:19
msgid ""
"[`consistency`](design.md#consistency): Do similar things the same way; "
"follow an existing convention rather than coining a competing one."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:20
msgid ""
"[`rust-native`](design.md#rust-native): Learn from Linux's design, not its C "
"idioms; write idiomatic Rust."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:22
msgid "**[Process](process.md)**"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:23
msgid ""
"[`imperative-subject`](process.md#imperative-subject): Write each commit "
"subject in the imperative mood, ≤72 chars, verb-first (\"Fix\", \"Add\", "
"\"Remove\"); backtick identifiers."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:24
msgid ""
"[`atomic-commits`](process.md#atomic-commits): One logical change per "
"commit; don't mix unrelated changes."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:25
msgid ""
"[`refactor-then-feature`](process.md#refactor-then-feature): Put preparatory "
"refactoring in its own earlier commit(s), separate from the feature."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:26
msgid ""
"[`focused-prs`](process.md#focused-prs): Keep a PR on a single topic; ensure "
"CI passes before requesting review."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:28
msgid "**[Naming](naming.md)**"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:29
msgid ""
"[`descriptive-names`](naming.md#descriptive-names): Names convey meaning at "
"the point of use; avoid single letters and ambiguous abbreviations."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:30
msgid ""
"[`accurate-names`](naming.md#accurate-names): Avoid names that mislead about "
"meaning, behavior, or side effects."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:31
msgid ""
"[`encode-units`](naming.md#encode-units): When the type doesn't carry the "
"unit, put it in the name (`timeout_ns`, `size_pages`)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:32
msgid ""
"[`bool-names`](naming.md#bool-names): Name booleans as positive assertions "
"(`is_`/`has_`/`can_`/…); avoid negation."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:33
msgid ""
"[`error-message-format`](naming.md#error-message-format): Lowercase start "
"(unless a proper noun), specific, Linux man-page style for syscall errors."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:35
msgid "**[Layout](layout.md)**"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:36
msgid ""
"[`top-down-reading`](layout.md#top-down-reading): Order a file top-down: "
"entry points and core flow first, detail below."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:37
msgid ""
"[`logical-paragraphs`](layout.md#logical-paragraphs): Group related "
"statements into blank-line-separated paragraphs, each one sub-step."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:39
msgid "**[Comments](comments.md)**"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:40
msgid ""
"[`explain-why`](comments.md#explain-why): Comments explain intent (why), not "
"what the code does; if you must explain \"what\", rewrite the code."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:41
msgid ""
"[`design-decisions`](comments.md#design-decisions): Document non-obvious "
"choices, with rationale and alternatives considered."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:42
msgid ""
"[`cite-sources`](comments.md#cite-sources): Cite the source (POSIX, Linux "
"man page, hardware manual, paper) for spec/algorithm behavior."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:44
msgid "**[Rust-Specific](rust-specific/)**"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:45
msgid "[Naming](rust-specific/naming.md)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:46
msgid ""
"[`camel-case-acronyms`](rust-specific/naming.md#camel-case-acronyms): Use "
"Rust CamelCase with title-cased acronyms (`Nvme`, not `NVME`)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:47
msgid ""
"[`closure-fn-suffix`](rust-specific/naming.md#closure-fn-suffix): End a "
"variable holding a closure or fn pointer with `_fn`."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:48
msgid "[Crates & Modules](rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:49
msgid ""
"[`workspace-deps`](rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md#workspace-deps): "
"Declare shared dependencies in `[workspace.dependencies]` and reference them "
"with `.workspace = true`."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:50
msgid ""
"[`module-docs`](rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md#module-docs): Open a "
"major module with a `//!` doc: purpose, key types, relation to neighbors."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:51
msgid ""
"[`narrow-visibility`](rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md#narrow-"
"visibility): Start private; widen visibility only when an actual consumer "
"requires it."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:52
msgid ""
"[`qualified-fn-imports`](rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md#qualified-fn-"
"imports): Import the parent module and call free functions/statics through "
"it, not by bare name."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:53
msgid "[Types & Traits](rust-specific/types-and-traits.md)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:54
msgid ""
"[`rust-type-invariants`](rust-specific/types-and-traits.md#rust-type-"
"invariants): Use the type system (newtypes, enums, generics) to make illegal "
"states unrepresentable."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:55
msgid ""
"[`enum-over-dyn`](rust-specific/types-and-traits.md#enum-over-dyn): For a "
"closed set of variants, prefer an `enum` over `Box<dyn Trait>`."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:56
msgid ""
"[`getter-encapsulation`](rust-specific/types-and-traits.md#getter-"
"encapsulation): Prefer a getter over a public field; it preserves naming "
"freedom and room for invariants."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:57
msgid "[Functions & Methods](rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:58
msgid ""
"[`no-bool-args`](rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md#no-bool-args): Avoid "
"boolean parameters that select behavior; split the function or use a typed "
"enum."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:59
msgid ""
"[`block-expressions`](rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md#block-"
"expressions): Use a block expression to scope temporary state that only "
"produces one value."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:60
msgid ""
"[`minimize-nesting`](rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md#minimize-"
"nesting): Flatten nesting past ~3 levels with early returns, guard clauses, "
"`let…else`, `?`, `continue`."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:61
msgid ""
"[`explain-variables`](rust-specific/functions-and-methods.md#explain-"
"variables): Bind intermediate results of a complex expression to well-named "
"variables."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:62
msgid "[Attributes & Macros](rust-specific/attributes-and-macros.md)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:63
msgid ""
"[`expect-dead-code`](rust-specific/attributes-and-macros.md#expect-dead-"
"code): Allow `#[expect(dead_code)]` only for a planned, clear, simple future "
"use."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:64
msgid ""
"[`alphabetical-attrs`](rust-specific/attributes-and-macros.md#alphabetical-"
"attrs): Sort outer attributes alphabetically; place `#[derive(...)]` last "
"with sorted traits."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:65
msgid ""
"[`narrow-lint-suppression`](rust-specific/attributes-and-macros.md#narrow-"
"lint-suppression): Suppress a lint at the narrowest scope (item/method), not "
"a whole type or module."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:66
msgid ""
"[`macros-as-last-resort`](rust-specific/attributes-and-macros.md#macros-as-"
"last-resort): Prefer functions and generics; use a macro only when the type "
"system can't express the need."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:67
msgid "[Comments](rust-specific/comments.md)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:68
msgid ""
"[`rfc1574-summary`](rust-specific/comments.md#rfc1574-summary): First doc "
"line is one sentence — a third-person verb for functions, a noun phrase for "
"types/modules."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:69
msgid ""
"[`comment-punctuation`](rust-specific/comments.md#comment-punctuation): End "
"full-sentence comments with terminal punctuation."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:70
msgid ""
"[`backtick-identifiers`](rust-specific/comments.md#backtick-identifiers): "
"Wrap identifiers in doc comments in backticks; prefer rustdoc links where "
"possible."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:71
msgid ""
"[`no-impl-in-docs`](rust-specific/comments.md#no-impl-in-docs): Doc comments "
"describe what an API does and how to use it, not its internal implementation."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/index.md:73
msgid "No **path-specific** guidelines yet."
msgstr ""
